<section>
    <h2>Normal Distribution</h2>
    <p>
        Normal distribution is a continuous distribution that is symmetric about the mean.
    </p>

    <div class="chart">
        <svg width="400" height="200">
            <path d="M20 160 Q200 20 380 160" fill="none" stroke="#16a34a" stroke-width="3"/>
        </svg>
        <p><b>Fig:</b> Normal Distribution Curve</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Hypothesis Testing – Basic Idea</h2>
    <p>
        Hypothesis testing is a statistical method used to make decisions using sample data.
    </p>

    <div class="chart">
        <svg width="400" height="140">
            <rect x="20" y="40" width="120" height="40" fill="#fde68a"/>
            <text x="40" y="65">Null Hypothesis</text>

            <line x1="140" y1="60" x2="200" y2="60" stroke="black"/>

            <rect x="200" y="40" width="120" height="40" fill="#bbf7d0"/>
            <text x="220" y="65">Decision</text>
        </svg>
        <p><b>Fig:</b> Hypothesis Testing Flow</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Test for Proportion</h2>
    <p>
        Hypothesis test for proportion checks whether a population proportion differs
        from a specified value.
    </p>

    <div class="chart">
        <svg width="400" height="120">
            <line x1="50" y1="60" x2="350" y2="60" stroke="black"/>
            <line x1="200" y1="40" x2="200" y2="80" stroke="red" stroke-width="2"/>
        </svg>
        <p><b>Fig:</b> Z-test for Proportion</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Test for Mean (Single Sample)</h2>
    <p>
        This test checks whether the sample mean differs significantly from the
        population mean.
    </p>

    <div class="chart">
        <svg width="400" height="150">
            <path d="M20 120 Q200 20 380 120" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="3"/>
            <line x1="200" y1="20" x2="200" y2="120" stroke="red"/>
        </svg>
        <p><b>Fig:</b> Z-test for Single Mean</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Test for Difference of Means</h2>
    <p>
        This test compares two population means to determine if there is a significant
        difference between them.
    </p>

    <div class="chart">
        <svg width="400" height="150">
            <path d="M20 120 Q150 40 280 120" fill="none" stroke="#16a34a" stroke-width="3"/>
            <path d="M120 120 Q250 40 380 120" fill="none" stroke="#dc2626" stroke-width="3"/>
        </svg>
        <p><b>Fig:</b> Difference of Two Means</p>
    </div>
</section>

